Axial tilt ?° Albedo 0.04 (assumed) Surface temp. {| cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" border="0" min mean max ~64 K (estimate) Prospero is a small retrograde non- spherical moon of Uranus found on 1999-07-18 by the astrophysicist Matthew Holman and his team, and given designation S/1999 U 3\. Confirmed as Uranus XVIII it was named after the sorcerer Prospero in William Shakespeare's play The Tempest. The orbital parameters suggest that it may belong, together with Sycorax and Setebos to the same dynamic cluster, suggesting common origin. Grav, Tommy; Holman, Matthew J.; Gladman, Brett J.; Aksnes, Kaare Photometric survey of the irregular satellites,Icarus, 166,(2003), pp. 33-45.
